#  Hospitality Process Optimization – Guest Check-in Improvement

##  Project Overview
This project focuses on optimizing the **guest check-in process** in a luxury hospitality environment. The objective was to reduce guest wait time, improve operational efficiency, and enhance overall guest experience.

This project was executed as part of independent consulting work under **Dreamfinity Consulting & Academy**.

---

##  Problem Statement
The existing check-in process was time-consuming and inefficient:
- Average check-in time: **12–15 minutes**
- Long queues during peak hours
- Manual verification and data entry
- Lack of real-time coordination with housekeeping

This resulted in poor guest experience and operational delays.

---

##  AS-IS Process (Current State)

1. Guest arrival  
2. Manual reservation lookup  
3. ID verification  
4. Room allocation  
5. Payment processing  
6. Key issuance  

### Key Issues Identified:
- Manual and repetitive data entry  
- No pre-check-in system  
- Delays due to room readiness uncertainty  
- Lack of inter-department coordination  

---

##  TO-BE Process (Optimized State)

1. Digital pre-check-in before arrival  
2. Auto-verification of guest details  
3. Real-time room status integration  
4. Quick key issuance at front desk  

### Improvements:
- Reduced manual effort  
- Faster processing  
- Improved coordination between front desk and housekeeping  

---

##  Impact & Outcomes

| Metric | Before | After |
|------|--------|-------|
| Check-in Time | 12–15 mins | <5 mins |
| Guest Wait Time | High | Significantly Reduced |
| Process Efficiency | Low | Improved |

